latestPosts.caption:
In the quiet chaos of bad days, when emotions crash like waves,
and no one seems to understand the storm within —
you’ll find that healing doesn’t always come wrapped in warm hugs or familiar faces.
Sometimes, those you love won’t show up,
but your one friend might sit with your rants like they were poetry.
It’s okay to feel too much, to cry without reason,
to break and bloom all on your own.
Because at the end of it all, it’s you —
choosing yourself, again and again,
in messy moods and healing silences.
